	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />My super nes worked fine the last time I used it years ago but now when you power it on all you get is a is a quick flash of color with then a BSOD without a cart in you get nothing at all.
<br />
<br />Apperintly this is a common problem  as its whats wrong with all the broken ones on ebay, how do I fix it?

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


	<hr width="85%" />

	<table width="85%" cellspacing="3" cellpadding="0" border="0" align="center">
	<tr>
		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Author:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b>blargg</b> [ Sat Feb 21, 2009 5:46 pm ]</td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Post subject:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b></b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Sorry, "BSOD" is not at all clear. Run these tests and give the results:
<br />
<br />1) What do you see when the SNES is disconnected from your TV with the TV on?
<br />2) What do you see when the SNES is connected to your TV, the TV on but the SNES off?
<br />3) What do you see when the SNES is connected and on, but without a cartridge in it?
<br />4) What do you see when the SNES is connected and on, with a cartridge in it?
<br />
<br />What do you see = what appears on screen and whether the power LED is lighted (old-style SNES only).

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


